00:00:02.340 --> 00:00:04.210
MALE SPEAKER: And welcome
to another talk at

00:00:04.210 --> 00:00:05.227
Google Experience.

00:00:05.227 --> 00:00:06.810
If you're here in
the audience, you've

00:00:06.810 --> 00:00:09.880
probably seen how amazing
the restaurant is yourself,

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:13.870
down in the North Beach,
Tony's Pizza Napoletana--

00:00:13.870 --> 00:00:16.379
as I feign my way
through Italian.

00:00:16.379 --> 00:00:18.570
But we have the man
himself here today.

00:00:18.570 --> 00:00:21.260
He's here to speak to us
about his new book, "The Pizza

00:00:21.260 --> 00:00:23.380
Bible," which is
everything it says

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:27.290
it is, the ultimate guide to the
variety and diversity of pizzas

00:00:27.290 --> 00:00:30.130
throughout the world, with
special advice for the home

00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:31.350
chef, as well.

00:00:31.350 --> 00:00:34.320
Tony's Pizza is a San
Francisco institution,

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:37.930
a thing of pure legend, and
he himself has won, I think,

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:40.170
11 international pizza awards.

00:00:40.170 --> 00:00:43.500
And then, I guess they decided,
to be fair to the other people,

00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:46.570
to elect him out
of the competition.

00:00:46.570 --> 00:00:49.810
So he's a judge in
emeritus now, I guess.

00:00:49.810 --> 00:00:51.510
So without further
ado, looks like we

00:00:51.510 --> 00:00:53.460
have some dough on the line.

00:00:53.460 --> 00:00:55.480
So please join me in
welcoming Tony to Google.

00:00:55.480 --> 00:00:55.980
Thank you.

00:00:55.980 --> 00:00:56.634
Thank you.

00:00:56.634 --> 00:00:57.134
Thanks.

00:00:57.134 --> 00:00:58.625
